b'Nominations for 2019 Provost\xe2\x80\x99s Excellence in Undergraduate Advising Awards'
b'\n\t\t\t\tNovember 29, 2018\t\t\t'
b'Dear Faculty, Staff and Students,'
b'It is my pleasure to announce the opening of the nomination period for the \xc2\xa02019 Provost\xe2\x80\x99s Excellence in Undergraduate Advising Award.\xc2\xa0 This award was established in 2011 to recognize professional advisors who have demonstrated exemplary skill in academic advising and a commitment to student success at the University of Illinois at Chicago.'
b'I invite you to nominate an individual who has made a significant contribution to academic advising at UIC by completing the online form at http://go.uic.edu/AdvisingAdwards no later than December 10, 2018.'
b'http://go.uic.edu/AdvisingAdwards'
b'Eligible nominees include non-faculty professionals who spend a significant portion of their job advising undergraduates, including academic advisors in the colleges and departments as well as counselors in academic support/success programs. \xc2\xa0Nominees must have served as advisors at UIC for at least one full academic year. Award recipients may be selected for the award no more than once every three years. Up to three awards of $750 are given annually.'
b'If you have additional questions, please contact Ms. Clare K. Delaney at clared@uic.edu.'
b'clared@uic.edu'
b'Sincerely,'
b'Susan Poser\nProvost and Vice Chancellor for Academic Affairs'
b'\xc2\xa0'
b'For more information, please contact:\nClare Delaney\nclared@uic.edu'
b'clared@uic.edu'
